From the foundational adiabatic equation $P V^gamma = "constant"$, we can substitute variables using the ideal gas law ($P prop T/V$ or $V prop T/P$):
  
  - Substituting $P$:
    $ (T / V) V^gamma = "constant" => T V^(gamma - 1) = C_1 $
    
  - Substituting $V$:
    $ P (T / P)^gamma = "constant" => T^gamma / P^(gamma - 1) = "constant" $
    Taking the $1/gamma$ root of both sides yields:
    $ T / P^((gamma - 1)/gamma) = T / P^(1 - 1/gamma) = C_2 $